cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR 

This paper focuses on learning high-level visual representations using a multi-task deep network and synthetic imagery. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses unsupervised feature space domain adaptation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of synthetic imagery for training the network also relates to robotics (cs.RO) and graphics (cs.GR) as these fields often use synthetic data for training and simulation.
